    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="1006"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.01/12–1944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister to Syria and Lebanon</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-01T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 1, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. We understand from the British Embassy that you and Shone have discussed the
                    instructions sent him by the Foreign Office on January <pb facs="1050" n="1038"
                        xml:id="pg_1038"/> 26 and that you agree in considering the representations
                    called for therein inopportune in the present local atmosphere. We should
                    appreciate your urgent comment on this, as the Department is inclined to agree
                    with the British views set forth therein. Please review the memorandum of
                    conversation with Mr. Chamoun on December 15,<note n="20" xml:id="d1006fn20"
                        >Camille Chamoun, Lebanese Minister in the United Kingdom; memorandum of
                        conversation not printed.</note> copy of which was sent to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
